    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1846-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1846-06-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="46" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d46">
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#center">
                        <hi rend="italic">Extract from the speech
                                    of Mr. Cass, of Michigan, in the Senate</hi>, <date ana="#date_imprecise-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1846-06-30" notBefore="1846-06-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">June,</hi>
                                1846</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>* * * “We are seeking a doubtful good, at the certainty of a great
                            sacrifice.” * * * “Those who believe that our title to all Oregon is so
                            ‘clear and unquestionable’ that no portion of it ought to be
                            relinquished, may well contend for its whole extent, and risk the
                            consequences.” * * *<seg type="margin">To accept the line of 49°
                                regarded as a sacrifice.</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
